      "content": "it just feels like a heavy weight i can't carry anymore. when you say \"letting go might be the only way to find peace\"... it makes me think that maybe the only actual way to stop the struggle is to just give up entirely. like, if the \"self\" is what's broken, then maybe there's no point in trying to save it. do you really think there's any value in continuing to exist when you're just a shell of a person?",
